# Encounter Creation Guidelines

## Location Framework

### Historical Context
- Previous events that shaped the area
- Former purpose/use of the location
- Recent changes or disturbances
- Local legends or stories

### Environmental Description
- General atmosphere and mood
- Weather conditions
- Time of day effects
- Ambient sounds/smells

### Terrain Features
- Natural formations
- Architectural elements
- Hazardous areas
- Cover/concealment options

## Points of Interest

### Primary Features
- Major landmarks
- Critical objectives
- Story-relevant locations
- Unique environmental elements

### Secondary Features
- Resource locations
- Rest areas
- Alternative paths
- Hidden secrets

### Dynamic Elements
- Moving hazards
- Changing conditions
- Time-sensitive features
- Environmental triggers

## Obstacles

### Environmental Challenges
- Natural barriers
- Weather effects
- Terrain hazards
- Visibility issues

### Tactical Challenges
- Enemy positions
- Patrol routes
- Defensive structures
- Traps/security measures

### Puzzle Elements
- Physical barriers requiring specific solutions
- Environmental puzzles
- Resource management challenges
- Time-based challenges

## Mapping Guidelines

### Scale Considerations
- Room-by-room detail for indoor areas
- Zone-based for outdoor locations
- Clear measurement references
- Height/depth indicators

### Map Symbols
▲ Elevation Change
◆ Point of Interest
⬟ Hazard
⬡ Resource
✧ Secret
≈ Water
▅ Cover
⬢ Enemy Position

### Map Layers
1. Base terrain/architecture
2. Environmental features
3. Dynamic elements
4. Points of interest
5. Enemy positions/patrol routes

### Navigation Elements
- Clear entry/exit points
- Major pathways
- Alternative routes
- Chokepoints
- Escape routes

## Encounter Balance

### Difficulty Factors
- Number of enemies
- Environmental hazards
- Resource availability
- Time constraints

### Pacing Elements
- Rest opportunities
- Resource distribution
- Challenge escalation
- Alternative solutions

### Reward Distribution
- Primary objectives
- Secondary discoveries
- Hidden treasures
- Environmental resources

## Documentation Format

### Header Information
- Location name
- Difficulty rating
- Recommended level/group size
- Time estimate

### Section Organization
1. Historical Context
2. Current State
3. Key Locations
4. Active Threats
5. Objectives
6. Resources
7. Special Notes

### Visual Aids
- Main map
- Detail sketches
- Enemy placement diagrams
- Hazard indicators
